Russians warned about fake calls from banks
In Russia, the number of calls from scammers that replace the phone number of the bank has increased.
This is reported by "Kommersant" with reference to the data of the Central Bank.
In the summer of 2019, the regulator handed over to telecom operators information about more than 2,500 numbers from which customers of various financial organizations were called.
In 189 cases, operators found a change of number.
Another 218 rooms were blocked, and in 59 cases, they set a restriction on the use of financial services.
Deputy head of the department of information security of the Central Bank Artem Sychev said that a wide range of Russian banks faced the replacement of the number.
He explained that operators do not always respond to the Central Bank’s warnings about fraudulent calls, citing the absence of such an obligation in the Law on Communications.
In the Bank "Opening", Rosbank and Alfa-Bank confirmed the information about the increase in the number of fraudulent calls with a change of number.
As reported in the press service of “Beeline”, part of the information about fraudulent calls, which was transmitted by the Central Bank, was incorrect: the lists included numbers that are really used by banks to communicate with customers.
Blocking them would lead to disruption of the organization.
Artem Sychev said that the Central Bank plans to create a database of numbers of fraudsters, which the telecom operator will contact with each call to check the number.
He explained that the establishment of such a base would require amendments to the legislation.
