Currently, the participants of the action, replacing each other, stand, holding in their hands a poster with the inscription “Freedom to all” and the names of the convicted and arrested after the uncoordinated rallies in Moscow in the summer of 2019.
In addition to Ustinov, on the poster the names of Egor Zhukov, Kirill Zhukov, Danylo Beglets, Evgeny Kovalenko, Konstantin Kotov, Ivan Podkopaev, Aidar Gubaidulin, Alexey Minyailo, Sergei Fomin, Samariddin Rajabov, Nikita Chirtsov, Eduard Malyshevsky,
On September 16, the Tver court in Moscow sentenced 24-year-old Ustinov to 3.5 years in a general-regime colony on charges of using violence against a soldier of OMON Rosgvardia at an uncoordinated action on August 3 in the center of Moscow (part 2. Article 318 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation).
After that, on September 20, at the request of the Prosecutor General's Office, the court changed Ustinov's measure of restraint from detention to a non-departure subscription.
Thus, the petition for Ustinov’s release received more than 112 thousand signatures per day.
Artists of theatre and cinema have started a flashmob in support of their colleague.
To participate in a single picket in solidarity with the actor on September 18, a queue was lined up on the Old Square.
Human rights defenders, journalists, scientists, teachers, doctors, Orthodox priests demanded a review of the case.
As reported to Interfax, Sister Ustinova Yulia, at a rally on September 29 in the capital in support of the defendants of the “Moscow case” her brother does not plan to speak.
The supply of “sanctions” to Russia fell 100 times
The government of the Russian Federation estimated that the supply of agricultural products and food to Russia from the countries that fell under the Russian food embargo, has decreased by more than 100 times since 2013.
According to a report sent to Russian President Vladimir Putin, in the first half of 2019, 31 thousand tons of products were imported from the sanctions countries against 3 million 442.2 thousand tons for the same period in 2013, Interfax reported.
At the same time, the cost of imported products decreased to $226.5 million from $4 billion to 975.5 million, respectively.
It is about the supply of goods that did not fall under the embargo.
As indicated in the report, the volumes of products banned for import were compensated by an increase in imports from the CIS countries, Africa, Southeast Asia, Serbia.
At the end of August, the government extended until December 31, 2020 the rules for the destruction of agricultural products, raw materials and foodstuffs, which are prohibited from importing into Russia as part of counter-sanctions.
The document, posted on the official portal of legal information, noted that the validity of the rules was extended for another year - from December 31, 2019 to December 31, 2020.
Initially, the decree on the destruction of sanctions applied to products from the United States, the EU, Australia, Norway and Canada.
Later, since August 13, 2015, Albania, Montenegro, Iceland, Liechtenstein have joined this list, and since January 1, 2016 - Ukraine.
The decree signed by Putin on the destruction of illegally imported “sanctions” (products that fell under the food embargo that Moscow imposed in response to the anti-Russian sanctions of the West) came into force in 2015.
In turn, the government allowed the destruction of “sanction” food in any legal way.
As Western sanctions continue, Russia has also extended its retaliatory measures.
At the same time, this measure does not apply to products that citizens import for personal use.
The ban does not apply to the import of goods for personal consumption weighing up to 5 kilograms.
However, the head of the Council under the President of the Russian Federation for the development of civil society and human rights Mikhail Fedotov earlier called the destruction of food “just immoral”, and this, according to him, negatively affects the education of people.
Moreover, Rospotrebnadzor took the initiative to ban the destruction of food products suitable for consumption in early June.
After that, a similar recommendation to the government was given by the Human Rights Council under the President of the Russian Federation.
And Deputy Prime Minister of the Russian Federation Alexey Gordeev said that it is wrong to destroy food products, and you need to think about how you can use them for their intended purpose, assessing the quality.
The head of the company was found guilty of tax evasion
By another verdict of the Leninsky District Court of Cheboksary, the director of the Land and Law LLC, Vyacheslav Morozov, was found guilty of committing crimes provided for in clause "b" of part 2 of Article 199 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation (evasion of taxes from the organization by including in the tax declaration deliberately false information, committed in a particularly large amount) and part 2 of Article 3 of the Criminal Code.
This is reported by the press service of the Investigative Department of the TFR in Chuvashia.
From January 2008 to December 2009, Vyacheslav Morozov entered into the tax accounting documents of LLC information on imperfect transactions.
According to fictitious documents, the company carried additional costs, and, therefore, the amount of taxes on value added and profit of the organization was reduced 11.2 million rubles.
Vyacheslav Morozov was sentenced to 3.5 years of probation.
By 2023, the first school of the new format will open in the center of the capital
The new school will be opened in Hamovniki.
According to the head of Moskomstroyinvest Anastasia Pyatova, all conditions for self-realization and development of children’s talents will be created there.
The educational institution decided to call "New Look".
This project will be supervised by the Moscow State Institute of International Relations of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Russia and the Foundation "Economic Development of Higher School".
The design of the building with an area of about 10 thousand "squares" is planned to begin next year.
They will finish construction at the end of 2022, and next year they will begin to recruit the first students.
"The project envisages the creation of a public, non-profit educational space, which will be based on the traditions of the classical Moscow school and experimental techniques," the press service of Moskomstroyinvest said.
